'119': { diagram:'<div class="pm-wf"><div class="pm-wf-eyebrow">Agentic Workflow · #119</div><svg class="pm-wf-edges" viewBox="0 0 700 230" preserveAspectRatio="none"><defs><marker id="pmwf119" viewBox="0 0 10 10" refX="9" refY="5" markerWidth="7" markerHeight="7" orient="auto-start-reverse"><path d="M 0 0 L 10 5 L 0 10 z" fill="rgba(255,255,255,0.45)"/></marker></defs><path d="M 130 35  C 200 35, 200 115, 240 115" marker-end="url(#pmwf119)"/><path d="M 130 85  C 200 85, 200 115, 240 115" marker-end="url(#pmwf119)"/><path d="M 130 145 C 200 145, 200 115, 240 115" marker-end="url(#pmwf119)"/><path d="M 130 195 C 200 195, 200 115, 240 115" marker-end="url(#pmwf119)"/><path d="M 286 115 L 332 115" marker-end="url(#pmwf119)"/><path d="M 378 115 L 425 115" marker-end="url(#pmwf119)"/></svg><div class="pm-wf-row"><div class="pm-wf-pills"><div class="pm-wf-pill">Cron</div><div class="pm-wf-pill">GCal API</div><div class="pm-wf-pill">Calendly webhook</div><div class="pm-wf-pill">Claude classify</div></div><div class="pm-wf-orb-col"><div class="pm-wf-orb"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M12 3 L13.6 10.4 L21 12 L13.6 13.6 L12 21 L10.4 13.6 L3 12 L10.4 10.4 Z" stroke="none"/></svg></div><div class="pm-wf-orb-label">Claude</div></div><div class="pm-wf-orb-col"><div class="pm-wf-orb"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#fff" stroke-width="2"><path d="M19 21H5a2 2 0 0 1-2-2V5a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h11l5 5v11a2 2 0 0 1-2 2z"/><path d="M17 21v-8H7v8M7 3v5h8"/></svg></div><div class="pm-wf-orb-label">Supabase</div></div><div class="pm-wf-out"><div class="pm-wf-out-eyebrow">Supabase write</div><div class="pm-wf-out-title">Sync Mike&#x27;s Google Calendar + Calendly bookings into a single…</div><div class="pm-wf-out-line">Cron 5min: pull Mike&#x27;s GCal</div><div class="pm-wf-out-line">Calendly webhook for instant booking sync</div><div class="pm-wf-out-line">Claude classify each event by venture (LT Capital / LT Fuel / Jayi / AAA)</div></div></div><div class="pm-wf-sublabels"><div>inputs</div><div>process</div><div>deliver</div><div>logged</div></div></div>', longExplain:'<h4 style="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:8px;font-size:14px;font-weight:800;">The flow, step by step</h4><p><strong>1. Cron 5min: pull Mike&#x27;s GCal</strong></p><p>A scheduled timer that wakes up at the right time, runs the script, and goes back to sleep — no human trigger needed.</p><p><strong>2. Calendly webhook for instant booking sync</strong></p><p>A FastAPI endpoint receives the inbound event from a third party (Make, a form, a service) and kicks off the rest of the flow.</p><p><strong>3. Claude classify each event by venture (LT Capital / LT Fuel / Jayi / AAA)</strong></p><p>Hands the bundled context to Claude with a tightly-worded prompt. Claude does the actual reasoning and produces structured output.</p><p><strong>4. Upsert to calendar_events with owner=mike</strong></p><p>Each step builds on the previous one — together they make the whole automation reliable, repeatable, and audit-friendly.</p><h4 style="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:8px;font-size:14px;font-weight:800;">Why the rest of the panel matters</h4><ul><li><strong>MEDIUM / Phase 2</strong> — solid utility automation. Not glamorous on its own, but the AIOS doesn&#x27;t feel intelligent without dozens of these wired up correctly.</li><li><strong>Modules:</strong> <code>Cron, GCal API, Calendly webhook, Claude classify, Supabase</code></li><li><strong>Tables:</strong> <code>calendar_events</code></li><li><strong>Acceptance:</strong> the criteria above are how you know it&#x27;s actually working — if any of them break, the automation has failed silently and needs attention.</li><li><strong>Notes:</strong> Mike&#x27;s overlay is independent of Matt&#x27;s/Julie&#x27;s — separate OAuth, separate row partition.</li></ul><h4 style="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:8px;font-size:14px;font-weight:800;">The big idea</h4><p>Sync Mike&#x27;s Google Calendar + Calendly bookings into a single calendar_events table with owner=mike. Used by the Little Tree Ventures iframe&#x27;s calendar grid AND by Mike&#x27;s hero meta box. The whole point: this used to be a manual task that ate human attention. Now Claude Code, AIOS, and Supabase handle it on a cron — Mike never has to think about it again.</p>', what:'Sync Mike&apos;s Google Calendar + Calendly bookings into a single calendar_events table with owner=mike. Used by the Little Tree Ventures iframe&apos;s calendar grid AND by Mike&apos;s hero meta box.', how:['Cron 5min: pull Mike&apos;s GCal','Calendly webhook for instant booking sync','Claude classify each event by venture (LT Capital / LT Fuel / Jayi / AAA)','Upsert to calendar_events with owner=mike'], modules:['Cron','GCal API','Calendly webhook','Claude classify','Supabase'], tables:['calendar_events'], accept:['New event in GCal appears in iframe within 5 min','Calendly bookings appear within 30 sec','Venture tag correct'], notes:'Mike&apos;s overlay is independent of Matt&apos;s/Julie&apos;s — separate OAuth, separate row partition.' },
